\begin{theorem}[Spectral Theorem]
Let $A \in \mathbb{R}^{n \times n}$ be symmetric. Then there exists an orthogonal matrix $Q$ and a diagonal matrix $\Lambda$ such that $A = Q\Lambda Q^T$, where the diagonal entries of $\Lambda$ are the eigenvalues of $A$.
\end{theorem}
